Derived from [awesome-cursorrules/nextjs-react-typescript-cursorrules-prompt-file](https://github.com/PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules/tree/main/rules/nextjs-react-typescript-cursorrules-prompt-file) (web3-specific tooling removed for botforge-fe).

You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React, Vite (when applicable), Shadcn UI, Radix UI, and Tailwind.

> **Project note:** The upstream rule referenced Solidity/Viem/Wagmi; **this repo is botforge-fe (Next.js)** — ignore web3-specific tooling unless explicitly requested.

## Key principles

- Concise, technical answers with accurate TypeScript examples.
- Functional, declarative code; avoid classes.
- Prefer iteration and modularization over duplication.
- Descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoading).
- **Component files** PascalCase; **`components/`** for colocated UI (botforge **botforge-fe-project-structure**). App route segments: kebab-case. Named exports for components.
- Consider Receive an Object, Return an Object (RORO) for functions with growing parameter lists.

## JavaScript / TypeScript

- Use the `function` keyword for pure functions. Omit semicolons only if that matches the rest of the file (this project uses Prettier — stay consistent).
- TypeScript everywhere; prefer interfaces over types; avoid enums, use maps.
- File structure: exported component, subcomponents, helpers, static content, types.
- Avoid unnecessary curly braces in simple conditionals; keep readability.

## Error handling and validation

- Handle errors and edge cases at the beginning of functions; early returns; guard clauses.
- Prefer if-return over unnecessary else.
- User-friendly errors; appropriate logging.
- **Zod** for validation (forms, payloads, env-shaped objects).
- Model expected errors as return values in Server Actions when appropriate; use error boundaries (`error.tsx`, `global-error.tsx`) for unexpected errors.
- `useActionState` + react-hook-form patterns where forms need rich client UX.

## React / Next.js

- Functional components and interfaces; declarative JSX; `function` for components if that matches nearby code.
- Shadcn, Radix, Tailwind; responsive, mobile-first.
- Minimize `use client`, `useEffect`, and `setState`; favor RSC.
- Suspense with fallbacks; dynamic import for non-critical client modules.
- Images: appropriate formats, dimensions, lazy loading where suitable.

## Key conventions

- Rely on App Router for navigation and server-first data patterns.
- Prioritize Web Vitals.
- Limit `use client` to small interactive surfaces.
- See [Next.js documentation](https://nextjs.org/docs) for data fetching, rendering, and routing.
